{"title":"5G is ‘ now’ eating cable’s lunch","link":"https://om.co/2024/02/20/5g-is-now-eating-cables-lunch/","date":1708447936000,"content":"<figure><img width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1583602621722-cbd1130b210b?ixid=M3wxMzczOTd8MHwxfGFsbHx8fHx8fHx8fDE3MDg0NDc4MzR8&amp;ixlib=rb-4.0.3&amp;fm=jpg&amp;q=85&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=1024&amp;h=683\" alt=\"black metal tower under white sky\" srcset=\"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1583602621722-cbd1130b210b?ixid=M3wxMzczOTd8MHwxfGFsbHx8fHx8fHx8fDE3MDg0NDc4MzR8&amp;ixlib=rb-4.0.3&amp;fm=jpg&amp;q=85&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=300&amp;h=200 300w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1583602621722-cbd1130b210b?ixid=M3wxMzczOTd8MHwxfGFsbHx8fHx8fHx8fDE3MDg0NDc4MzR8&amp;ixlib=rb-4.0.3&amp;fm=jpg&amp;q=85&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=1024&amp;h=682 1024w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1583602621722-cbd1130b210b?ixid=M3wxMzczOTd8MHwxfGFsbHx8fHx8fHx8fDE3MDg0NDc4MzR8&amp;ixlib=rb-4.0.3&amp;fm=jpg&amp;q=85&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=150&amp;h=100 150w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1583602621722-cbd1130b210b?ixid=M3wxMzczOTd8MHwxfGFsbHx8fHx8fHx8fDE3MDg0NDc4MzR8&amp;ixlib=rb-4.0.3&amp;fm=jpg&amp;q=85&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=768&amp;h=512 768w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1583602621722-cbd1130b210b?ixid=M3wxMzczOTd8MHwxfGFsbHx8fHx8fHx8fDE3MDg0NDc4MzR8&amp;ixlib=rb-4.0.3&amp;fm=jpg&amp;q=85&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=1536&amp;h=1024 1536w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1583602621722-cbd1130b210b?ixid=M3wxMzczOTd8MHwxfGFsbHx8fHx8fHx8fDE3MDg0NDc4MzR8&amp;ixlib=rb-4.0.3&amp;fm=jpg&amp;q=85&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=2048&amp;h=1365 2048w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1583602621722-cbd1130b210b?ixid=M3wxMzczOTd8MHwxfGFsbHx8fHx8fHx8fDE3MDg0NDc4MzR8&amp;ixlib=rb-4.0.3&amp;fm=jpg&amp;q=85&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=256&amp;h=170 256w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1583602621722-cbd1130b210b?ixid=M3wxMzczOTd8MHwxfGFsbHx8fHx8fHx8fDE3MDg0NDc4MzR8&amp;ixlib=rb-4.0.3&amp;fm=jpg&amp;q=85&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=2000&amp;h=1333 2000w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1583602621722-cbd1130b210b?ixid=M3wxMzczOTd8MHwxfGFsbHx8fHx8fHx8fDE3MDg0NDc4MzR8&amp;ixlib=rb-4.0.3&amp;fm=jpg&amp;q=85&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=192&amp;h=128 192w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1583602621722-cbd1130b210b?ixid=M3wxMzczOTd8MHwxfGFsbHx8fHx8fHx8fDE3MDg0NDc4MzR8&amp;ixlib=rb-4.0.3&amp;fm=jpg&amp;q=85&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=1100&amp;h=733 1100w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1583602621722-cbd1130b210b?ixid=M3wxMzczOTd8MHwxfGFsbHx8fHx8fHx8fDE3MDg0NDc4MzR8&amp;ixlib=rb-4.0.3&amp;fm=jpg&amp;q=85&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=232&amp;h=154 232w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1583602621722-cbd1130b210b?ixid=M3wxMzczOTd8MHwxfGFsbHx8fHx8fHx8fDE3MDg0NDc4MzR8&amp;ixlib=rb-4.0.3&amp;fm=jpg&amp;q=85&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=627&amp;h=416 627w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1583602621722-cbd1130b210b?ixid=M3wxMzczOTd8MHwxfGFsbHx8fHx8fHx8fDE3MDg0NDc4MzR8&amp;ixlib=rb-4.0.3&amp;fm=jpg&amp;q=85&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=560&amp;h=373 560w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1583602621722-cbd1130b210b?ixid=M3wxMzczOTd8MHwxfGFsbHx8fHx8fHx8fDE3MDg0NDc4MzR8&amp;ixlib=rb-4.0.3&amp;fm=jpg&amp;q=85&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=1800&amp;h=1200 1800w\" /><figcaption>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@jan_huber\">Jan Huber</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/?utm_source=on-my-om&amp;utm_medium=referral\">Unsplash</a> </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It is not uncommon to hear the question: what is 5G really good for? After all, it doesn’t change the current applications, it doesn’t change our mobile experience too much from the more advanced version of LTE mobile broadband that is widely available around the world. So, again, what is 5G good for?</p>\n\n\n\n<span></span>\n\n\n\n<p>How about broadband access to the home? The 5G Fixed Wireless Access has become increasingly popular — as <a href=\"https://om.co/2023/11/14/what-5g-fixed-wireless-boom-can-teach-us-about-technology/\" target=\"_blank\">I explained in this article last year. Most</a> of this growth is coming at the expense of traditional broadband providers. Initially, the traditional landline companies lost subscribers. And now the cable-based broadband providers are coming under pressure. And they are worried. Peter Kafka <a href=\"https://www.businessinsider.com/broadband-internet-super-bowl-ad-spectrum-tmobile-fixed-wireless-cable-2024-2\">points out</a> that they are responding with Super Bowl ads.</p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>The broadband guys are happy to tell you why they think their internet is better than the wireless internet the telco guys are selling. But spending <a href=\"https://www.businessinsider.com/temu-spends-millions-super-bowl-ads-effort-win-us-users-2024-2\" target=\"_blank\">Super Bowl ad money</a> to do that? That’s pretty telling.</p>\n<cite>Kafka in Business Insider</cite></blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>The cable broadband providers have gone from dominating the “net new subscribers” category to getting demolished at the hands of 5G Fixed Wireless providers, primarily T-Mobile and Verizon in fourteen quarters.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"1024\" height=\"497\" src=\"https://149366103.v2.pressablecdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/IMG_3307-1024x497.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://149366103.v2.pressablecdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/IMG_3307-1024x497.jpeg 1024w, https://149366103.v2.pressablecdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/IMG_3307-300x146.jpeg 300w, https://149366103.v2.pressablecdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/IMG_3307-768x373.jpeg 768w, https://149366103.v2.pressablecdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/IMG_3307-1536x745.jpeg 1536w, https://149366103.v2.pressablecdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/IMG_3307-2048x993.jpeg 2048w, https://149366103.v2.pressablecdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/IMG_3307-192x93.jpeg 192w, https://149366103.v2.pressablecdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/IMG_3307-1100x534.jpeg 1100w, https://149366103.v2.pressablecdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/IMG_3307-560x272.jpeg 560w, https://149366103.v2.pressablecdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/IMG_3307-1800x873.jpeg 1800w\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Chetan Sharma (of Chetan Sharma Consulting) pointed out that during the fourth quarter of 2023, Comcast and Charter, two major cable providers, lost 96,000 subscribers. Meanwhile, the two major 5G fixed wireless broadband providers, T-Mobile and Verizon, added 916,000 net new broadband subscribers, bringing their total for 2023 to about 3.75 million.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>According to Bruce Leichtman, president and principal analyst for Leichtman Research Group, fixed wireless services have accounted for 101% of the approximately 3,625,000 net broadband additions over the past year. It would be very interesting to see how the cable companies counteract this threat of the decoupling of content and the connection.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><a href=\"https://om.co/2023/11/14/what-5g-fixed-wireless-boom-can-teach-us-about-technology/\">A Fixed Wireless Boom 20 Years In The Making</a></blockquote>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>February 20, 2024. San Francisco</em></p>","author":"Om Malik","siteTitle":"Om Malik","siteHash":"56aa7c22de1a9e5680d03082a2a13db78fe214c96b8119e8d54042cbf2d355ae","entryHash":"af5eab6d1c677ec89d484170fc3c18626d34c3dc948fec5f75009476735ccc33","category":"default"}